::Across the border

You don't cross through the same hole in the concrete that you did last time. There are a few different ways across, and you have to be careful about using too many of the same ones. There's this place, where the barbed wire has grown loose and thin, where you can crawl underneath it. You throw a rope ladder over from the other side, letting Kurt scramble up and over himself. Once he's safely across the border, you pull the ladder back and stash it away, careful to hide it well. No one on this side of the wall cares about people trying to get over it, but they will steal a perfectly decent rope ladder if it's just lying around.

This part of Under is not quite as nice as the one the school is in. There's a corporation that controls this particular block that doesn't particularly care about upkeep, which means that it's a little cheap and rundown. The sidewalks are overgrown with weeds, and graffiti tags on the various walls. There's nothing much to steal, so the gangs don't run through as often.

Kurt's eyes are wide and startled as he follows you. "Wow," he says.

You grab his hand so he won't wander off by himself. "Come on," you say. "I know a shortcut."

